### ============================================================================
### MedBridge Agent — End-to-End Tests (reflab routing)
### ============================================================================
###
### Every request starts from lab-core: http://localhost:8000/service-requests
### Lab-core spawns a daemon thread that calls the agent asynchronously.
### Wait ~15s between tests for background processing.
###
### Setup (run once before this file):
###
###   1. Clear the mapping cache:
###        docker compose exec agents python3 -c "
###        from database import SessionLocal
###        from models.mapping_cache import MappingCache
###        db = SessionLocal()
###        n = db.query(MappingCache).filter(MappingCache.system_target=='reflab').delete()
###        db.commit(); print(f'deleted {n} rows'); db.close()
###        "
###
###   2. Insert the ERR-LOINC exam (needed for Test 3):
###        docker compose exec labcore python3 -c "
###        from database import SessionLocal
###        from models.exam_catalog import ExamCatalog
###        db = SessionLocal()
###        e = db.query(ExamCatalog).filter(ExamCatalog.exam_code=='ERR-LOINC').first()
###        if not e:
###            exam = ExamCatalog(id='b9e7d142-3a65-4f81-bc29-8d4ef6a7c910',
###                exam_code='ERR-LOINC', exam_name='Teste LOINC desconhecido',
###                category='external', can_perform=False,
###                requires_support_lab=True, support_lab='REFLAB', turnaround_hours=168)
###            db.add(exam); db.commit(); print('inserted')
###        else: print('already exists')
###        db.close()
###        "
###
### Legend:
###   external exam (can_perform=false, support_lab=REFLAB) → lab-core routes to agent
###   internal exam (can_perform=true)  → lab-core handles directly, no agent
###
### Test order: 1 → 2 → 3
###   Test 1 populates the cache (create_exam → reflab mapping)
###   Test 2 reuses cache, different values, still succeeds
###   Test 3 reuses cache, ERR-LOINC triggers reflab 404, agent detects + reports
### ============================================================================

### ============================================================================
### TEST 1 — First call to reflab (cache miss → doc_reader → build → success)
### ============================================================================
### Lab-core creates SR with external exam ONC001.
### Agent: cache MISS → doc_reader reads integration docs → builds FHIR Bundle
### → POST to reflab (201) → saves mapping to cache → writes FHIR Task.
###
### Expected:
###   lab-core: 201 Created
###   agent logs: cache_hit=False → sent → 201 → cache saved → FHIR Task created
### ============================================================================
POST http://localhost:8000/service-requests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patient_id": "11c5be47-3215-4890-a79f-9c2b2293a85e",
  "practitioner_id": "0f7f838f-5bbd-43b7-951c-02582e4272a3",
  "priority": "ROUTINE",
  "notes": "Test 1 — cache miss, doc_reader builds FHIR Bundle",
  "items": [
    { "exam_code": "ONC001", "exam_name": "Marcadores Tumorais" }
  ]
}

### ============================================================================
### TEST 2 — Second call (cache hit → send_direct → success)
### ============================================================================
### Same operation (create_exam) and target (reflab) as Test 1,
### different patient, practitioner, and exam code (GEN001).
### Agent reuses the cached FHIR Bundle schema — injects GEN001 + new
### patient/practitioner into the FHIR entry — no doc_reader or LLM needed.
###
### Expected:
###   lab-core: 201 Created
###   agent logs: cache_hit=True → sent → 201 → cache updated use_count=1
### ============================================================================
POST http://localhost:8000/service-requests
Content-Type: application/json

{
